<br>
On big raids I am a heavily armed 7-11 (probably just tipped off who I am to a few people <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ).<br>
<br>
Mages summon the following:<br>
<br>
Food/Water<br>
Mod Rods<br>
WR bags (at 51, a mage can summon a 10 slot, Giant 100% WR 0.0 bag... most monks want them if they don't have better).<br>
Mod Rods<br>
Throwing and Missile weapons.<br>
Foci.<br>
Resist Gear (Elemental Binkies for everyone)<br>
Mod Rods<br>
Late Players (Call of Hero)<br>
Tank Mezzing pets<br>
Mod Rods<br>
<br>
Since Luclin came out, I've played my mage for about 3 months full time... I have probably summoned a million MR2s. I have lost a full level worth of 60 xp mod rodding to death and then some (NEVER start a MR2 run up with ANYTHING in your effects area flashing, btw)<br>
<br>
Pets... Enchanters get REALLY pissy about mage pets because of the mez breaking. Mage pets STILL break mezzes... my suggestion: use earth pets on raids. The root is only 15 seconds, rarely sticks on mobs where root will affect aggro, and root does no damage. With pets no longer aggroing mobs... ALWAYS have your earth pet out unless you are using Eye of Tallon (it makes you invisible and kills your pet...), know when to pull it off... always keep its buffs updated... if you get a rogue unmezzable mob... the Earth Pet is the Tank Mez that Never Dies. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uroninsenshi.showPublicProfile?language=EN>RoninSenshi</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://members.aol.com/sageofthehalo/Kanji.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Senshi No Adakia</span><br>  Posts: 678<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(6/26/02 9:34:28 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=892.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/sageofthehalo/Kanji.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: I'm not a mage...</span><hr size=1> From a Dueling Prespective, their are Two Classes that pretty much knock me around like a Little Female Sailor Scout trying to defeat the Negaverse..<br>
