<br>
As for grouping, it really depends on the situation you are in.  Before the patch, it was very much dependent on the pathing of where you are fighting.  Not so much now.  Pet not agroing and pet not breaking mez, helped all pet classed greatly.  <br>
<br>
As a lvl 60 sorcereer told me.  Wizard are for raids, but mages are for both.  Sure a wiz can out nuke us on raids.  That is not our role.  Grods is first priority.  At least I know that my pet is doing dmg while laying rods down.  On big raids, my pet is doing the best dmg of all other pets, and sometimes outdamaging the under 60 melee.  I still get my nukes in too.  Can't wait for SCF3 <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
In groups, wizards can't touch us.  Sure they can KS a kill, but in the long haul, we prevail.  Can you deny a 33 pt damage shields, a pet doing dmg, a nuker, and those Grods <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> .  Don't forget, mages increase the casting ability of all the casters in the group, be in reducing cast time, increase nuke dmg, or reduction of mana.<br>
<br>
Now that I am done with my Magician Propaganda speech, let me get back on topic.  <br>
<br>
